comments.body:
Docker fails with the same error.

I guess this depends on the definition of "internal". Comparing the documentation of --internal, the intent of docker seems clearer to me.

- Docker: Restrict external access **to** the network
- Podman: Restrict external access **of** this network

I was hoping it might be supported by CNI, as there is this snipped in the internal-net:
`            {
                "capabilities": {
                    "portMappings": true
                },
                "type": "portmap"
            },
`


Do you have any other ideas how to expose ports without allowing internet access? It might be possible to use macvlan to attach the network to an isolated bridge, but macvlan is deprecated.

@basilgello: What do you mean by "private network"? 

- If it is `--internal `: it doesn't work, see my first post ;) 
- if it is -o parent=privateBridge: I assumed macvlan was deprecated completely, upon rereading the manpage it seems only the **option** --macvlan is deprecated. If macvlan stays, its exactly what I am looking for.
